<statement><div><p>The perimeter of a rhombus is <m>{1620}\,\text{m}</m>. One of its diagonals is <m>{486}\,\text{m}</m>. Answer the following:</p>
<p>
</p><ol type="a">
  <li>
    <p>Find the length of the other diagonal.</p>
    <p><m>\text{The other diagonal} = </m> <fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/> <m>\text{m}</m>  </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Find the area of the rhombus.</p>
    <p><m>\text{Area} = </m> <fillin characters="7" name="ans2"/> <m>\text{m}^2</m>  </p>
  </li>
</ol>
</div></statement>
<solution><div><p>To answer the above question follow the following steps</p>
<p><alert>Step 1: Find the length of one side</alert></p>
<p>A rhombus has 4 equal sides. Therefore, <br/>
<md>
<mrow>\text{Perimeter} \amp =4 \times \text{side}</mrow>
<mrow>{1620} \amp =4 \times \text{side}</mrow>
<mrow>\text{side}=\frac{{1620}}{4}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp ={405}\, \text{m}</mrow>
</md>
</p>
<p><alert>Step 2: Use the diagonal property</alert></p>
<p>The diagonals of a rhombus cut each other into two equal parts and form right angles.<br/>
<m>\bullet</m> One diagonal <m>={486}\, \text{m}</m>, so half of it <m>=\frac{{486}}{2}={243}</m>.<br/>
<m>\bullet</m> Let the other diagonal <m>=d_2</m>. Then half of it <m>= \frac{d_2}{2}</m>.

</p>
<p>Using Pythagorasâ€™ Theorem:<br/>
<md>
<mrow>{405}^2\amp = \left (  \frac{{486}}{2}\right )^2+\left (  \frac{d_2}{2}\right )^2</mrow>
<mrow>\left (  \frac{d_2}{2}\right )^2\amp ={405}^2- \left ({243}  \right )^2</mrow>
<mrow>d_2\amp =2 \times \sqrt{  {405}^2-  \left ({243}  \right )^2    }</mrow>
<mrow>\text{So, the other diagonal is:}</mrow>
<mrow>d_2\amp ={648}\,\text{m}</mrow>
</md>
</p>
<p><alert>Step 3: Find the area of the rhombus</alert></p>
<p>The formula for the area is: <m>\text{Area}=\frac{d_1 \times d_2}{2}</m> <br/> Therefore;</p>
<p><md>
<mrow>\text{Area}\amp =\frac{{486} \times {648}}{2}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp ={157464}\, \text{m}^2</mrow>
</md></p>

<p>Therefore: <br/>
The length of the other diagonal is: <m>{648}\,\text{m} </m><br/>
The area of the rhombus is: <m> {157464}\, \text{m}^2</m></p></div></solution>
<answer><p><m>648</m></p></answer>
<answer><p><m>157464</m></p></answer>
